      "question": "If two positive integers $x$ and $y$ are expressed as $x = p^2q^3$ and $y = p^3q$, where $p$ and $q$ are prime numbers, then the value of $\\text{HCF}(x, y)$ is:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the prime factorisation of $x$ and $y$.",
          "Recall that the HCF of two numbers is the product of the smallest power of each common prime factor involved in the numbers.",
          "Identify the common prime factors as $p$ and $q$.",
          "The smallest power of $p$ in $x$ and $y$ is $p^2$.",
          "The smallest power of $q$ in $x$ and $y$ is $q^1$.",
          "Therefore, the $\\text{HCF}(x, y) = p^2 \\times q = p^2q$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x = p^2q^3 \\\\ y = p^3q \\\\ \\text{HCF}(x, y) = p^{\\min(2, 3)} \\times q^{\\min(3, 1)} \\\\ \\text{HCF}(x, y) = p^2 \\times q^1 = p^2q$"
      },
